OBJECTIVE

The purpose of this document is to describe the testing strategy used to validate tenant isolation in the Multi-Tenant SaaS POS Backend system.

Tenant isolation ensures that:

Data belonging to one tenant cannot be accessed by another tenant.

All database queries are filtered using tenant_id.

No cross-tenant data leakage occurs.

SCOPE

This document covers:

Repository layer isolation testing

Service layer isolation testing

Direct SQL validation

Integration testing using Testcontainers

API-level tenant validation

TENANT ISOLATION OVERVIEW

The system enforces tenant isolation using:

tenant_id column in all tenant-specific tables

Tenant context management (ThreadLocal or SecurityContext)

Repository-level filtering

Integration tests with PostgreSQL Testcontainers

Each request must contain a tenant identifier (from JWT or request header).

TESTING APPROACH

Testing tools used:

JUnit 5

Spring Boot Test

Testcontainers (PostgreSQL)

Maven Surefire

JaCoCo for coverage validation

